                                        <div data-id="2839-fwa-termsAndConditions"><p>If you are (1) a legal resident of the 50 United States and D.C. and (2) 18 years of age or older, on a 5G Home Ultimate, 5G Home Plus, 5G Home, LTE Home Plus, LTE Home Internet, Verizon Home Internet Lite or Verizon Home Internet Lite Extra plan, you are eligible to purchase the $13/mo “Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads)” plan perk, which includes access to Netflix Standard with Ads and HBO Max Basic with Ads.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">One offer per VHI plan.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">Billing begins upon enrollment. Activation of line/internet service required. Access to the Netflix and HBO Max streaming services begins upon registering each of the two services separately.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true"><b>Netflix</b>: In order to enjoy the Netflix service as part of your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk, you will need to register the Netflix service by completing the Netflix registration process. You will receive instructions on how to begin registering the Netflix service via text message.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">If you already have an existing Netflix account, you can link it to your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk when you register Netflix as part of your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk. You will continue to be charged separately for any existing Netflix account until you link that account to your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk. For any queries regarding your billing with Netflix for your existing Netflix account, please contact Netflix directly.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">If you link an existing Netflix account to your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk, terminating the Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk or switching between content options as part of your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk will not automatically cancel your Netflix membership, and Netflix will automatically resume charging your existing payment method that they have on file once your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk ends. If you wish to review the details of your Netflix membership, please visit the “Account” pages on the Netflix website.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">If you change your subscription from the Netflix Standard with Ads tier that comes with your Verizon perk to any other Netflix subscription level, you will be charged the difference between the then-current retail plan price of Netflix Standard with Ads and your selected Netflix subscription level, and billed by Verizon as the seller of the item on your Verizon bill.
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">If and to the extent that the Netflix Terms of Use related to billing, payments and cancellations conflict with the terms of your customer contract with Verizon, the latter shall prevail with the exception of the terms regarding updates to payment methods (currently Section 3.3 of the Netflix Terms of Use).
<br aria-hidden="true">
<br aria-hidden="true">Verizon will share your mobile telephone number and/or email address with Netflix to facilitate your registration of the Netflix service included in your Netflix &amp; HBO Max (With Ads) perk. For further information about how Verizon handles your personal data, please visit the Privacy Notice available on <a target="_blank" href="/home/internet/5g/privacy/" tabindex="-1">verizon.com/privacy</a>. You can view Netflix’s Privacy Statement on <a target="_blank" href="https://www.netflix.com/privacy" tabindex="-1">netflix.com/privacy</a>.
<br aria-hidden="true">
